  "text": "The analysis of correlation identified a practically complete dependence between the activity of soil dehydrogenases and the content of Pb (r = 0.829, p \\ 0.05), Ni (r = 0.908, p \\ 0.05) as well as Cd (r = 0.917, p \\ 0.05), which must have been a result of a lack of a negative effect of heavy metals on the activity of enzymatic proteins of microorganisms. Neither the count nor the species diversity of microorganisms being the source of soil enzymes changed. The natural content of heavy metals did not cause oxidative stress [CITATION_1] , and so there occurred no inhibition of the activity of dehydrogenases and soil catalase. Heavy metals at low concentrations can stimulate the development of microorganisms and thus the activity of enzymes in soil.",
